COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. Ira ABRAHAM, Respondent. No. 8148. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 19, 1936. Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Atty. Gen., and Herman Oliphant, Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. William F. Peters, for respondent.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of petitioner, consented to by counsel for respondent, ordered, petition to review dismissed; mandate forthwith.
